cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.RO

The paper proposes a novel method for autonomously decomposing tasks in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also leverages association rule mining, which is a subfield of data mining, making cs.DM (Data Mining) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with hierarchical methods, which are often used in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with multi-task reinforcement learning, which involves the coordination of multiple agents, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the efficiency and performance of the proposed method, which involves optimization and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category as well.
